parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulator can cause the window to suddenly fall into the door, making it difficult or impossible to operate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver and passengers stranded.
symptoms: The window falls into the door
the window does not roll up or down
the window regulator makes a popping or banging noise
the window is stuck in the down position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sunroof can cause it to not close properly, which can lead to water damage, noise, and distraction while driving.
symptoms: The sunroof does not close properly
the sunroof makes a loud noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank and Filler Neck Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank and filler neck can cause fuel to spill back out during fueling, leading to a fire risk and environmental hazards.
symptoms: Fuel spills back out during fueling
fuel gushes out of the filler neck
fuel splashes out of the filler neck
fuel spills all over the vehicle and surrounding area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair the rear structure reinforcement can lead to a fuel tank leak in the event of a rear-end collision, resulting in a fire risk.
symptoms: Dealership failure to repair the rear structure reinforcement
lack of parts availability
delayed repair
and incomplete repair.
